main event: A UFO sighting occurred at Whidbey NAS, Whidbey Island, Washington on 17th February 1959. The observation involved a round, blue-green object, approximately the size of a dime, lasting around 1-6 seconds. The report concluded that it was likely a balloon or a fireball.
interesting points: The sighting lasted only 1-6 seconds, indicating a brief and fleeting observation.
The object was described as round, blue-green, and the size of a dime, providing specific details about the appearance of the UFO.
The document mentions the evaluation of fairly reliable personnel but notes that weather conditions were not conducive to keen observation, raising questions about the reliability of the sighting.
The report indicates that there were no photographs of the UFO included, suggesting a lack of visual evidence for the observation.
It was noted that the sighting was observed by military personnel, including Corporals and a 2nd Lieutenant, adding credibility to the witnesses.
sighted object: round, blue-green object, size of a dime
witnesses: military personnel: Corporals and a 2nd Lieutenant
